00:13:11.326 --> 00:13:13.976 A:middle
from absolutely nothing, MARI
didn't compile on the Mac,

00:13:13.976 --> 00:13:17.916 A:middle
didn't run on the Mac, to
being able to demo here today

00:13:17.916 --> 00:13:19.746 A:middle
which you guys will be
seeing in a few minutes.

00:13:20.786 --> 00:13:24.556 A:middle
The screenshots you can see
on the screen were taken

00:13:24.556 --> 00:13:26.466 A:middle
about a week apart
by my developers

00:13:26.466 --> 00:13:28.166 A:middle
as they were bringing MARI up.

00:13:28.956 --> 00:13:31.866 A:middle
The first image is the
first time MARI ran

00:13:31.866 --> 00:13:33.046 A:middle
on the Mac in five years.

00:13:33.736 --> 00:13:35.056 A:middle
The second one is a week later.

00:13:35.136 --> 00:13:36.456 A:middle
We have rendering
up and working.

00:13:37.036 --> 00:13:40.896 A:middle
And the third one is a week
after that where we're dealing

00:13:40.896 --> 00:13:45.936 A:middle
with big datasets we can
paint and we can animate.

00:13:46.526 --> 00:13:49.816 A:middle
So it really has been a
pretty seamless process.

00:13:49.936 --> 00:13:52.706 A:middle
However, we have been incredibly
lucky during this whole

00:13:52.706 --> 00:13:55.246 A:middle
process-- have been given
access to the new Mac Pro.

00:13:56.496 --> 00:14:00.886 A:middle
We originally designed MARI
with multiple GPUs in mind.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:13:56.496 --> 00:14:00.886 A:middle
We originally designed MARI
with multiple GPUs in mind.

00:14:01.686 --> 00:14:05.486 A:middle
For me it makes so much sense
that you're going to want

00:14:05.486 --> 00:14:07.496 A:middle
to be processing
huge amounts of data

00:14:07.496 --> 00:14:09.886 A:middle
on one device while you're
displaying it fluidly

00:14:09.886 --> 00:14:12.396 A:middle
at 60 frames per
second on a second.

00:14:13.086 --> 00:14:16.896 A:middle
However, we've not really
ever seen a viable platform

00:14:16.896 --> 00:14:18.296 A:middle
for us to do this before.

00:14:18.856 --> 00:14:20.936 A:middle
We don't see multiple
GPUs installed

00:14:20.936 --> 00:14:22.556 A:middle
in visual effects
artist machines.

00:14:23.256 --> 00:14:25.696 A:middle
We see it in the
gaming world, you know,

00:14:25.696 --> 00:14:28.646 A:middle
people who put two GPUs
in their gaming rig

00:14:28.646 --> 00:14:31.686 A:middle
so they can play Gears
of War at 1080p 60 hertz.

00:14:32.316 --> 00:14:35.156 A:middle
But that power has never
been available to artists.

00:14:36.216 --> 00:14:40.036 A:middle
The multiple GPUs in the new
Mac Pro especially combined

00:14:40.036 --> 00:14:41.286 A:middle
with the updated OpenGL

00:14:41.286 --> 00:14:45.876 A:middle
and OpenCL support makes
it just a dream platform

00:14:45.876 --> 00:14:46.766 A:middle
for us to develop on it.

00:14:46.766 --> 00:14:49.996 A:middle
It's been really a
fantastic experience.

00:14:50.556 --> 00:14:53.316 A:middle
It's also going to make
my life a lot easier.

00:14:53.316 --> 00:14:56.786 A:middle
A large part of my job
is actually working

00:14:56.786 --> 00:15:00.356 A:middle
with our most demanding
customers to help them design

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:14:56.786 --> 00:15:00.356 A:middle
with our most demanding
customers to help them design

