where he still fit in the
world but was different

00:23:18.486 --> 00:23:19.286 A:middle
than all the other characters.

00:23:19.286 --> 00:23:22.036 A:middle
She again needed to be
scarier and yet still feel

00:23:22.036 --> 00:23:23.176 A:middle
like she came from
the same planet.

00:23:24.406 --> 00:23:27.816 A:middle
So once the design is settled,
it really gets passed in to kind

00:23:27.816 --> 00:23:28.876 A:middle
of two different areas.

00:23:28.876 --> 00:23:32.736 A:middle
The first is the modeling
department where, in this case,

00:23:32.736 --> 00:23:35.586 A:middle
Michael Honsel took this
design and began to sculpt it

00:23:35.586 --> 00:23:38.946 A:middle
on the computer, very much
how he would sculpt an object

00:23:38.946 --> 00:23:40.306 A:middle
in real life in real clay.

00:23:40.566 --> 00:23:42.386 A:middle
But he's sculpting it
digitally on the computer.

00:23:42.776 --> 00:23:45.476 A:middle
But it also gets passed to the
art department again to start

00:23:45.476 --> 00:23:48.056 A:middle
to develop the textural
look of the character.

00:23:48.636 --> 00:23:52.446 A:middle
And so this is a painting by
Shelly Wan and it was given

00:23:52.446 --> 00:23:55.606 A:middle
to me to show me,
OK, this is the way

00:23:55.606 --> 00:23:57.926 A:middle
that the surface should look
when it's reacting to light.

00:23:58.006 --> 00:24:00.726 A:middle
This is how the character
needs to look

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:23:58.006 --> 00:24:00.726 A:middle
This is how the character
needs to look

00:24:00.726 --> 00:24:03.016 A:middle
in color and with specularity.

00:24:03.016 --> 00:24:05.076 A:middle
And I'll explain some of
the details of that later.

00:24:05.586 --> 00:24:07.476 A:middle
And so we've got
this beautiful image.

00:24:08.396 --> 00:24:11.816 A:middle
And along with this image comes
a bunch of reference photography

00:24:11.816 --> 00:24:15.086 A:middle
of the different creatures that
make up what Hardscrabble is.

00:24:15.086 --> 00:24:18.676 A:middle
And so, we we start with
her makeup, you know,

00:24:18.676 --> 00:24:20.276 A:middle
and all these little
great details

00:24:20.276 --> 00:24:22.026 A:middle
about what her face makeup
is going to look like.

00:24:22.026 --> 00:24:24.396 A:middle
But then we moved into
her different aspects

00:24:24.396 --> 00:24:26.416 A:middle
like the horns, how those
are going to be shaped,

00:24:26.416 --> 00:24:28.846 A:middle
what the colors are going
to be, how shiny they are.

00:24:28.846 --> 00:24:30.566 A:middle
And we go through
all of these details

00:24:30.566 --> 00:24:31.626 A:middle
of these different aspects.

00:24:31.886 --> 00:24:34.526 A:middle
But one of the things about
her shells and her legs,

00:24:35.186 --> 00:24:38.056 A:middle
with a centipede that's only
this big, I mean only this big,

00:24:38.416 --> 00:24:41.276 A:middle
it has this sort of
translucency to it

00:24:41.346 --> 00:24:43.426 A:middle
but that would give her a
sense of being very small.

00:24:43.426 --> 00:24:47.536 A:middle
So instead of going with the
insect variety of shells,

00:24:47.536 --> 00:24:49.206 A:middle
we went with more
of a crustacean look

00:24:49.546 --> 00:24:51.766 A:middle
because that would indicate
a larger scale creature.

00:24:52.166 --> 00:24:55.046 A:middle
So we have these great images
of her legs, of the shells,

00:24:56.066 --> 00:24:58.366 A:middle
and also these great
batwings and the translucency

00:24:58.366 --> 00:24:59.696 A:middle
that we could get
with the batwings.

00:24:59.696 --> 00:25:00.836 A:middle
All these things
were thought about.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:24:59.696 --> 00:25:00.836 A:middle
All these things
were thought about.

00:25:01.606 --> 00:25:05.756 A:middle
But with this photography-- with
these images, I wasn't supposed

00:25:05.756 --> 00:25:09.496 A:middle
to take them and make a
photorealistic character.

00:25:09.786 --> 00:25:13.816 A:middle
The goal at Pixar is never to
go with just loads and loads

00:25:13.816 --> 00:25:16.186 A:middle
of detail and just make
it look like a creature

00:25:16.446 --> 00:25:19.246 A:middle
because we've hit this area
called "Uncanny Valley".

00:25:19.246 --> 00:25:22.136 A:middle
It's something we try to avoid
very much where you've added

00:25:22.136 --> 00:25:25.736 A:middle
so much detail that it
looks too realistic.

00:25:26.156 --> 00:25:30.126 A:middle
And at Pixar, we want to find
the essence of these designs.

00:25:30.126 --> 00:25:32.366 A:middle
We want to boil it down
to its simplest idea

00:25:32.366 --> 00:25:34.576 A:middle
and then really pull
that idea out.

00:25:34.806 --> 00:25:36.926 A:middle
And so with all these
photography, I was supposed

00:25:36.926 --> 00:25:39.326 A:middle
to take inspiration
but not copy exactly.

00:25:39.676 --> 00:25:42.166 A:middle
I was supposed to
find that simple idea.

00:25:42.986 --> 00:25:44.786 A:middle
So, the next thing
that we're going

00:25:44.786 --> 00:25:49.116 A:middle
to do is actually demonstrate
the process of how I began

00:25:49.116 --> 00:25:50.776 A:middle
to paint this character
on the computer.

