Now, again, I'm trying
to lay in some

00:28:07.746 --> 00:28:11.636 A:middle
of the bigger base details
first and then I'll start moving

00:28:11.636 --> 00:28:12.796 A:middle
into the smaller details.

00:28:12.796 --> 00:28:15.016 A:middle
You never want to start
with small details.

00:28:15.226 --> 00:28:16.456 A:middle
And any artist will
tell you this,

00:28:16.456 --> 00:28:19.656 A:middle
"If you start painting the
eyelashes before you've really,

00:28:19.656 --> 00:28:21.286 A:middle
you know, figured out
the shape of the head,

00:28:21.826 --> 00:28:23.086 A:middle
you're doing something wrong."

00:28:23.086 --> 00:28:26.166 A:middle
So I'm starting with the
big broad strokes first.

00:28:26.786 --> 00:28:29.496 A:middle
And this horn, if you remember
that image from the lizard,

00:28:30.246 --> 00:28:32.876 A:middle
it had some really nice
